lead_paragraph: A Russian spacecraft tumbled out of control after launching on Tuesday, threatening more than three tons of fuel, water, food and other supplies for the International Space Station.

headline.print_headline: Europe; Cargo for Space Station at Risk
headline.main: Cargo for Space Station at Risk

snippet: A Russian spacecraft tumbled out of control after launching on Tuesday, threatening more than three tons of fuel, water, food and other supplies for the International Space Station.
abstract: Russian spacecraft Progress 59 spins out of control after launch, endangering cargo of fuel, food and other supplies bound for International Space Station.
